2026-04-14 08:16:35,577 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: The sheet has data starting at column G (Slip start) and column H (Slip end), with the Book Number in column J. The user wants a lookup formula in cell B2 that takes a slip number entered in M5 and returns the corresponding Book Number, or the message "not found - please re-enter" if M5 is blank or the slip number does not fall within any defined range.

Because each book contains exactly 10 consecutive slips, the start numbers in column G are sorted ascending. We can use an approximate MATCH (type 1) to find the row where the start slip is the greatest value ≤ the lookup slip, then verify that the lookup slip is ≤ the end slip in column H. If the lookup slip is out of range or M5 is blank, we return the error message.

The formula (LibreOffice‑compatible) is:

```
=IF(M5="","not found - please re-enter",
   IFERROR(
      IF(M5>INDEX($H$6:$H$30, MATCH(M5,$G$6:$G$30,1)),
         "not found - please re-enter",
         INDEX($J$6:$J$30, MATCH(M5,$G$6:$G$30,1))
      ),
      "not found - please re-enter"
   )
)
```

We will write this string into B2, save the workbook to the output folder, run `recalculate`, then reload the file (data_only) and print B2 and M5 to verify the formula is in place.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter
import os

# Paths
input_path = '/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_56599_init.xlsx'
output_dir = '/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/'
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, '1_56599_init.xlsx')

# Load workbook (read/write)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # assume first sheet is the target

# Write the lookup formula into B2
formula = ('=IF(M5="","not found - please re-enter",'
           'IFERROR('
           'IF(M5>INDEX($H$6:$H$30, MATCH(M5,$G$6:$G$30,1)),'
           '"not found - please re-enter",'
           'INDEX($J$6:$J$30, MATCH(M5,$G$6:$G$30,1))'
           '),'
           '"not found - please re-enter"'
           ')')
ws['B2'].value = formula

# Save workbook to output location
wb.save(output_path)
print('Saved workbook with formula to', output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
recalc_result = await recalculate(output_path)
print('Recalculate result:', recalc_result)

# Reload with data_only to see cached values
wb2 = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws2 = wb2[ws.title]

print('B2 after recalculation (should be formula string or cached value):', ws2['B2'].value)
print('M5 current value (lookup input):', ws2['M5'].value)
```
